summary:
I don’t know if I’ve already said this, but New Year’s Day has to be my favourite song of Taylor’s ever.
Before I was born, my...
body:
I don’t know if I’ve already said this, but New Year’s Day has to be my favourite song of Taylor’s ever.

Before I was born, my mum would sit and play piano for me if I ever got restless inside her and it would calm me down immediately. Probably because when she plays you can hear and feel that she loves what she’s doing. Because of my parents, music is, without a doubt, one of the most important things in my life. Even today, at 18, whether it’s my mum playing piano, or my dad playing one of his many hand-made guitars, their music never fails to make me feel better. Even if I sit down to play piano or my flute, it releases an unbelievanle amount of stress.

I love New Year’s Day so much, because like my parents, when Taylor plays, whether it be guitar or piano, and obviously when she sings, you can feel how much she loves what she’s doing. To me, that love is more important than anything in this world. To be truly in love with what you do and be able to share it with the world is magical.

Taylor never fails to make me feel better and for that, I’ll be forever grateful.

Taylor, if you happen to be reading this, thank you, I love you 💕
